[Claim 1]
A method for producing tofu comprising:
comminuting a first mixture of soybeans and water until the volume-weighted median particle size of soybeans in the first mixture, as measured using dynamic light scattering, is 250 μm or less;
heating the comminuted first mixture;
separating the comminuted and heated first mixture into soymilk and okara; and
coagulating a second mixture of the soymilk and a coagulant to prepare tofu.
